Sure! Below is a simple HTML web app that meets your requirements. The app takes a 64-character string as input and applies the specified transformations.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>String Transformation</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        input, button {
            margin: 10px;
            padding: 10px;
        }
        #output {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Transform Your String</h1>
    <input type="text" id="inputString" placeholder="Enter a 64-character string" maxlength="64" />
    <button onclick="transformString()">Transform</button>
    <div id="output"></div>

    <script>
        function transformString() {
            const input = document.getElementById('inputString').value;
            if (input.length !== 64) {
                alert('Please enter exactly 64 characters.');
                return;
            }

            const transformed = Array.from(input).map((char, index) => {
                // Change '9' to '0'
                if (char === '9') return '0';

                // Change capital letters to lowercase
                if (char >= 'A' && char <= 'Z') return char.toLowerCase();

                // Change vowels to their acute accent form
                switch (char.toLowerCase()) {
                    case 'a': return 'á';
                    case 'e': return 'é';
                    case 'i': return 'í';
                    case 'o': return 'ó';
                    case 'u': return 'ú';
                    default: return char;
                }
            }).join('');

            document.getElementById('output').innerText = transformed;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Features and Explanation:
1. **Input Field:** The user can input a 64-character string.
2. **Transformation Logic:**
   - If the character is '9', it changes to '0'.
   - If the character is a capital letter (A-Z), it converts to lowercase (a-z).
   - If the character is a vowel (a, e, i, o, u), it transforms to its acute accent form (á, é, í, ó, ú).
3. **Output Display:** The transformed string is displayed below the input.

### Usage:
- Open the HTML file in a web browser.
- Enter a 64-character string and click the "Transform" button to see the transformed result.

Make sure to test it with different 64-character strings to see how the transformation rules are applied!
